	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64550595"><p>Funny that the first and second posts are about the same exact thing - that if you were to construct from scratch a system with only one goal, to pass the turning tests, LLMs are how you would do it.</p><p>They are built to output streams of words that are statistically the most likely word based on what other humans write.  So in response to almost anything, an LLM will produce a string of words that almost always look and read very human on the surface.</p><p>Not to mention, that just like real humans an LLM is capable<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

