		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64551393"><a href="https://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/activities/ieg/e-library/sources/t_article.pdf" title="ox.ac.uk">Computing machinery and Intelligence<span class="substr"> </span></a> [ox.ac.uk] by A. M. Turing<br> <br>

&lsquo;I propose to consider the question, "Can machines think?" This should
begin with definitions of the meaning of the terms "machine" and "think."<br> <br>

The definitions might be framed so as to reflect so far as possible the
normal use of the words, but this attitude is dangerous, If the meaning of the
words "machine" and "think" are to be found by examining how they are
commonly used it is difficult to escape the conclusion that the meaning and
the ans</div>
	</div>

